  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Rinse the chicken breast and pat it dry with paper towels.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together the jerk seasoning, olive oil, onion, bell pepper, toffee popcorn, honey, apple cider vinegar, hot sauce, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Rub the spice mixture all over the chicken breast, making sure to coat it evenly.",
    "Place the chicken breast on a hot stone plate and roast in the preheated oven for 30 minutes.",
    "After 30 minutes, remove the chicken from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes.",
    "Slice the chicken breast into thin strips and serve immediately.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh herbs, if desired."
